rs prompting the development of the relatively new sciences of forest pathology and nematology; and the teaching of plant pathology. Estey discusses early legislation in Canada pertaining to plant diseases and the faltering first steps toward international regulation, and provides a detailed history of mycology province by province.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMycologiexRecherchexHistoirexCanada. 0aMycologyxResearchxHistoryxCanada. 0aMycologyxResearchzCanadaxHistory. 0aPlant diseasesxResearchxHistoryxCanada. 0aPlant diseasesxResearchzCanadaxHistory. 0aPlant diseasesxStudy and teachingxHistoryxCanada. 0aPlant diseasesxStudy and teachingzCanadaxHistory. 0aPlantesxMaladies et fléauxxRecherchexHistoirexCanada. 0aPlantesxMaladies et fléauxxÉtude et enseignementxHistoirexCanadaxCanada. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356440440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773564404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773564404/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles